#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Nandiyasakkasutta → nandiyasuttaṃ (bj) | nandiya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Nandiyasakkasutta"
msgstr "40. Nandiya the Sakyan"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "sn55.40:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho nandiyo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nandiyo sakko "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Nandiya the Sakyan went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn55.40:1.3"
msgid ""
"“yasseva nu kho, bhante, ariyasāvakassa cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni sabbena "
"sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ natthi sveva nu kho, bhante, ariyasāvako "
"pamādavihārī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, if a noble disciple were to totally and utterly lack the four factors "
"of stream-entry, would they live negligently?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.398"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:2.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Yassa kho, nandiya, cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā "
"sabbaṃ natthi tamahaṃ bāhiro puthujjanapakkhe ṭhito’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Nandiya, someone who totally and utterly lacks these four factors of stream-"
"entry is an outsider who belongs with the ordinary persons, I say."

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.2"
msgid ""
"Api ca, nandiya, yathā ariyasāvako pamādavihārī ceva hoti, appamādavihārī ca "
msgstr ""
"Neverthless, Nandiya, as to how a noble disciple lives negligently and how "
"they live diligently, "

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.3"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "listen and attend closely, I will speak."

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho nandiyo sakko bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Nandiya replied."

msgctxt "sn55.40:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:3.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, nandiya, ariyasāvako pamādavihārī hoti?"
msgstr "“And how does a noble disciple live negligently?"

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.2"
msgid "Idha, nandiya, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.40:3.4"
msgid ""
"So tena buddhe aveccappasādena santuṭṭho na uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya, "
"rattiṃ paṭisallānāya."
msgstr ""
"They’re content with that confidence, and don’t make a further effort for "
"seclusion by day or solitude by night."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ pamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ na hoti."
msgstr "When they live negligently, there’s no joy."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.6"
msgid "Pāmojje asati, pīti na hoti."
msgstr "When there’s no joy, there’s no rapture."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.7"
msgid "Pītiyā asati, passaddhi na hoti."
msgstr "When there’s no rapture, there’s no tranquility."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.8"
msgid "Passaddhiyā asati, dukkhaṃ viharati."
msgstr "When there’s no tranquility, there’s suffering."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.9"
msgid "Dukkhino cittaṃ na samādhiyati."
msgstr "The mind that suffers doesn’t become immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.10"
msgid "Asamāhite citte dhammā na pātubhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When the mind is not immersed in samādhi, principles do not become clear."

msgctxt "sn55.40:3.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ apātubhāvā pamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"Because principles have not become clear, they’re reckoned to live "
"negligently."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nandiya, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.3"
msgid ""
"ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to "
"immersion."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.4"
msgid ""
"So tehi ariyakantehi sīlehi santuṭṭho na uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya "
"rattiṃ paṭisallānāya."
msgstr ""
"They’re content with that ethical conduct loved by the noble ones, and don’t "
"make a further effort for seclusion by day or solitude by night."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ pamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ na hoti."
msgstr "When they live negligently, there’s no joy."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.6"
msgid "Pāmojje asati, pīti na hoti."
msgstr "When there’s no joy, there’s no rapture."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.7"
msgid "Pītiyā asati, passaddhi na hoti."
msgstr "When there’s no rapture, there’s no tranquility."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.8"
msgid "Passaddhiyā asati, dukkhaṃ viharati."
msgstr "When there’s no tranquility, there’s suffering."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.9"
msgid "Dukkhino cittaṃ na samādhiyati."
msgstr "The mind that suffers doesn’t become immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.10"
msgid "Asamāhite citte dhammā na pātubhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When the mind is not immersed in samādhi, principles do not become clear."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ apātubhāvā pamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"Because principles have not become clear, they’re reckoned to live "
"negligently."

msgctxt "sn55.40:4.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, nandiya, ariyasāvako pamādavihārī hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple lives negligently."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.399"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, nandiya, ariyasāvako appamādavihārī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a noble disciple live diligently?"

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.2"
msgid "Idha, nandiya, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.4"
msgid ""
"So tena buddhe aveccappasādena asantuṭṭho uttari vāyamati divā pavivekāya "
"rattiṃ paṭisallānāya."
msgstr ""
"But they’re not content with that confidence, and make a further effort for "
"seclusion by day and solitude by night."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ appamattassa viharato pāmojjaṃ jāyati."
msgstr "When they live diligently, joy springs up."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.6"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati."
msgstr "Being joyful, rapture springs up."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.7"
msgid "Pītimanassa kāyo passambhati."
msgstr "When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.8"
msgid "Passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vediyati."
msgstr "When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.9"
msgid "Sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr "And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.10"
msgid "Samāhite citte dhammā pātubhavanti."
msgstr "When the mind is immersed in samādhi, principles become clear."

msgctxt "sn55.40:5.11"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ pātubhāvā appamādavihārītveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"Because principles have become clear, they’re reckoned to live diligently."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.40:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nandiya, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.40:6.3"
msgid ""
"ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
